result.execSummary:
All charges against Indira Gina Iree Hughlett in this case have been dismissed. These charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Indira Gina Iree Hughlett is presumed innocent.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Indira Gina Iree Hughlett in court.  
Samantha Raygo appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  
Deputy Court Clerk: rmm.  
Indigency hearing proceeded.  Court makes a finding that defendant is indigent.  Court appoints Christin Saint Pierre as counsel for defendant at the rate of $100.00 per hour.  Attorney Saint Pierre accepts appointment.  Defendant shall reimburse Milwaukee County at the rate of $100.00 on the 1st of every month, commencing 6/01/22 until paid in full. Failure to pay will result in a civil judgment and/or tax intercept or other means.  Case is adjourned to Br. 1.  Status conference scheduled for May 17, 2022 at 02:30 pm.

Signed and filed, No Contact Order.  Defendant to have no contact with MW.
No Weapons Order, signed and filed.

Court ordered $500 cash bail previously posted to be returned to the remitter. 
No possession of dangerous weapons or firearms.
Court ordered arrest warrant withdrawn.  Recall issued.

Defendant Indira Gina Iree Hughlett in court with attorney Stephen Andrew Sargent.  Mallory R Davis appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Defendant is advised that this case is assigned to Judge Davila, Branch 1. Court reviewed the complaint and found probable cause. Defendant received a copy of the complaint and was advised of right to counsel. Defendant does not qualify for Public Defender representation. Court entered a plea of not guilty on behalf of the Defendant. Court reserves Defendant's right to file a substitution of judge pursuant to Sec. 971.20 right to challenge probable cause and to have complaint read until Defendant's next scheduled court appearance. Case is adjourned for a Indigency Hearing in Branch 1.

  Indigency hearing scheduled for April 11, 2022 at 10:00 am.
Cash bond ordered to be forfeited in the amount of 500.00.
COURT ORDERED DEFENDANT REMANDED TO THE COMMISSIONER ON RETURN OF THE ARREST WARRANT.

Defendant Indira Gina Iree Hughlett not in court.  Michelle A. Grasso appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Defendant failing to appear, Court ordered an Arrest Warrant to be issued. Upon arrest, defendant is ordered remanded to a commissioner. Court ordered any bail on deposit to be forfeited. Court makes a finding that there is a possible victim identified and stays the forfeiture order with restitution to be determined at close of case.
